comment: zaho mosary means I am starving
Usually, the response is tsisy vaovao
In contrast to english it is used for both asking and apologizing
pronounced like mofu but u does not exist in malagasy
Acronym for jiro sy rano malagasy. Tsisy JIRAMA means there is no power... and maybe no water, too
used for last addition after connecting nouns with sy
Composed of tia (love) -ko (of me) and anao (you)
Literally the name of mine is Samuel as -ko is a genitive suffix
There is no problem, hakuna matata

english: to wake up, to get out of bed
A big bottle of water, please!
